Alhaji Mai Mala Buni and Prof. Babagana Umara Zulum along with their deputy governor have been sworn – in as new executive governor’s of Yobe and Borno States respectively. In Yobe State, the event was done at the Banquet Hall of the Government House Damaturu. The oath was administered by Justice Garba Musa Nabaruma, the Chief Judge of Yobe State. In Borno State, the event was held at the massive Ramat Square amidst hundreds of thousands of supporters with heavy security. Details later